'''Tennessee Civil War National Heritage Area''' is a federally designated [[National Heritage Area]] that encompasses the entire U.S. state of [[Tennessee]]. The heritage area concentrates on eight major corridors: the [[Mississippi River]], [[Cumberland River]], [[Tennessee River]], [[Louisville and Nashville Railroad]], [[Nashville and Chattanooga Railroad]], [[East Tennessee Georgia and Virginia Railroad]], [[Memphis and Charleston Railroad]] and the [[Nashville and Northwestern Railroad]] corridors.<ref name=mtsu1>{{cite web|title=Civil War Sites Open to the Public|url=http://www.tncivilwar.org/tour_the_ha/resources|publisher=Middle Tennessee State University|accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=mtsu3>{{cite web|title=Frequently Asked Questions|url=http://www.tncivilwar.org/who_we_are/FAQ|publisher=Middle Tennessee State University|accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>
The Tennessee Civil War National Heritage Area was designated in 1996. It is managed by the [[Middle Tennessee State University]] Center for Historic Preservation.<ref name=mtsu2>{{cite web|title=History of the Tennessee Civil War National Heritage Area|url=http://www.tncivilwar.org/who_we_are/history|publisher=Middle Tennessee State University|accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>
